		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=73&FN=Wizard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=383276&TN=Being+wizard+sucks&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=383285&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Well, frankly, after hearing some of the more specific information, and then looking at the spells and other things, I'm pretty well convinced that the Wizard class is BROKEN.<P>Magicians appear to have more powerful attack spells on a regular basis, although the wizard class is specifically supposed to be good at wrecking things.<P>Wizards get experience points at an impossibly slow rate.  Assaulting monsters with a party of other level 12 sword-slingers I regularly hear comments like "Wow!  Almost 1/2 bubble from that fight" while due to the higher exp-per-level requirements applied to wizards, I get a whole pixel if I'm lucky.<P>I also find that around levels 10-12 (where I am now) I'm pretty much *forced* to group, since anything that's going to give me experience without leaving me so weak that I can't defend myself against the next thing that shows up, stands a REALLY good chance of killing me.  It isn't a lot of fun playing a game that, even when you play as conservatively as possible (never go into a fight without FM/HP, always have your shield and damage shields on, just in case they get at you) you get killed literally every other fight.<P>Yes, it's great that you don't lose the ENTIRE amount of exp that you would have gotten from killing something if it kills you instead, but this three-steps-forward-and-two-steps-back approach has GOT to go.  I don't see how a game can be considered moderately realistic when you get killed in literally every other solo fight, because if you don't have someone else around to keep the blasted things off you so you can cast, the limited choice of weapons and armor means you DIE nearly every time.  Either the power of the offensive spells needs to be raised across the board, or the level requirements for wizards need to be lowered, because it's simply not worth the trouble to play a game where you MUST find a group to work with.  Even bards (who are pretty much designed for play with a group) can hold their own in a fist fight and play at the same time.<P>Actually, now that I think about it, a large number of the problems would go away if they would quit treating it like every single thing that hits you is a "bash", since bashing is mentioned in the documentation as something to be used to stop a spell-caster.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
