		<hr size="1">Ok, I completely agree with Dagmar D'Surreal.  I was thinking, so, maybe our power isnt as great as mages, or we don't have spells that can make us profit.  What I was thinking, was that we could have some special ability to research a gem and give us optimal usage of it, Say, We get a bonus to wearing items with gems in it, or we could somehow instill these gems with the power of our spells. This way, we could have some type of money making.  We also could have some better DD spells.  Honestly, The power of Magicians is their PETS, not themselves.  The power of Warriors is essentially thier Weapons.  The power of wizards should be themselves, they should be able to whip a magician, magicians Should have a more mediocre spell casting ability and their pets a slightly more advanced fighting.  The pets should be better than the actual caster, the caster should have weaker spells because of this.  NOW, Wizards have no pets, so, If they don't have pets, naturally you might think of them having superior spell damage, but this is not true.  The only exception to the rule is when wizards get ice comet, BUT!  how many of us have no life?  You can't expect an average joe like myself to spend 8 hours a day trying to get ice comet.  Getting level 49 is difficult, but increasing the difficulty to get the one spell that puts wizards ahead of magicians is like starting over again and getting to level 20.  I am just a level 10 wizard, but I also am starting to have some problems, I cannot defend from any attack, my melee never increases.  I must go into every single battle with full mana and hit points on the off chance that they should hit me. If I try to attack ANY creature that is white to me, and I FIZZLE, that is instant death. I have to conserve my mana such that I have one cast of root, which is completely ineffective at level ten because any old monster can resist it, so, that throws root out of the question, and i can't attempt to cast it again because that would land me a one way trip to my home point without my stuff and half my experience gone.  I am also seeing some problems when i'm attackin some creature on the side of a hill, When my bolt flys off it will hit, but the monster will sustain no damage, i will get no "target resisted" message BUT i do lose mana, therefore, I need to run to guards or accept my newfound death wish.  I really hate being a wizard, but I just have too much stuff and hours put into this one that i wouldn't want to go back.  Some of you may tell me to just shut up and quit whining and don't be a wizard if there is such a problem with it.  But, I used to be saying that same thing.  There were just too many little things that built up.  I mean, I should be awesome, I AM A WIZARD!  How many people think that wizards should be godly?  If you think about it,  how many times in any type of fantasy book has ANYONE been happy to HAVE to rid of a wizard?  NO ONE.  NO BODY WANTS TO MESS WITH A GUY THAT CAN SHOOT FLAMES OR ICE from his hands.  Our power may be limited by our mana, but we still should be able to kick some serious butt (PG Rating).  Magicians sound like some guy at a parlor shop that does card tricks.  I mean, Lets just think about this DO I WANT TO GO AND ATTACK A WIZARD?  NO.  You know what... This is what I propose..... Anyone that wants to help me petition this, I would love to hear about it because this idea would be awesome, Email Me at Chickencow@tomgreenshow.zzn.com for your support.  I SAY, that at a certain level in a Wizard's career, they can go 2 ways, they can split off and Become a WARLOCK or they can still continue their training and become a wizard, Wizard being the good guy, WARLOCK the contradictor.  Or something like that, I would just like to see the day in everquest when some level 45 druid walks up to a wizard of level 46 and just drops his jaw and rolls down the carpet in praise of "PULEASSSE DONT HURT ME."  Hey, All I gotta say to the Everquest team is this, If We level slower, and have twice the toughness  clawing our way up to the top, then we should have twice the rewards and should be some BAD Mothers with somthing to light up people with!  <P><BR>                          Lomianus<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
