		</font>
		<hr size="1">Wizards are NOT underpowered.  Certainly, they're not great at soloing, but then again most classes aren't.  At high levels, you HAVE to group to survive, there's no way to do it otherwise.  There are very few 50th level players who can even solo a level 46 mob...the game is just designed to work around groups.<P>When i'm grouped, 9 times out of 10 i deal more damage than anyone else in battle.  And that's with tanks who can be 3 or 4 levels higher than me.  There's no way you can claim that a wizard sucks at damage dealing.  Admittedly, the Rend spell is stupid and needs to be fixed, but aside from that most wizard spells are better in several ways than other classes spells of equivalent level.  The one slow period i've found is around level 20, where you get a crappy spell (force strike, resisted by everything that's not blue), and you have to rely on you level 16 spells (flame shock) until 24.<P>As for magicians, admittedly they do have dd spells that are almost as nice as ours...but they are quite a bit less mana efficient, have longer casting times, or take time to cycle.  It's hard to factor what you see on paper into the game unless you've played a magician...but trust me, it makes a significant difference in combat.  Even with their pet, i do quite a bit more damage in combat.<P>In terms of money making abilities, group teleport is one way you can make quite a bit of money....but honestly magicians can't make that much either off their spells...only enchanters have the ability to hoard immense amounts of money with enchanted jewelry.  And regardless, 1000pp (for a robe of the oracles) ain't that big of a deal for a level 30-something wizard....it's pricey, but well within reach.  Don't even try arguing about money vs. levels, tank classes are WAY more screwed in that respect....most of the items that are good for a specific level are only attainable 10 levels later...and they have a lot more they need to buy (full set of armor, weapons, etc.), while wizzes just have robes and maybe a few misc items.<P>Point is, every class has their benefits and disadvantages, and in most ways they're fairly well balanced (rogues might be an exception).  If you don't like your wizard, then play as another class instead.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
