		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 8/12/1999 9:56:00 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=73&FN=Wizard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=383276&TN=Being+wizard+sucks&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=383294&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">As a level 24 wizard a I have a few comments to make...<P>Personally I think the wizard class is not underpowered.  Of course I would LIKE to be more powerful, but who wouldn't?  As it stands now, I'm a very valuable member of any group I'm in, simply for the fact that I can burn mobs down fast.  <P>YES wizards are "weak" in the HP realm.  But that makes sense.  I mean, you spend all day with your nose in a book studying the arcane, not out training for physical combat.  We SHOULD be weak from that roleplaying standpoint.<P>And as for magicians being better, I think not!  Magician pets are puny compared to the mob's one can come up against when in a good group.  The magicians pet is one of his best powers, and his spells are second rate to a wizard's.  Magicians have their own place in the world, but for dealing out the most damage the fastest, the Wizard wins hands down.<P>Of course I won't complain if Verant decides to buff up the wizards.  I think we should be able to imbue ourselves with more powers definitely.  But then again if Verant leaves the wizards exactly as they are I won't complain.  The wizard is my first character, and I love the class to death  <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/smile.gif"><P>-Filladari Flaymeweever, 23rd Level Wizard on the Tarew Marr server<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
