		<hr size="1">A couple of things of note for the posters on this thread.  Mages are not that much weaker than wizards when it comes to DD.  Sure you have an extra second on casting times and recoveries.  The mana thing is almost non-existant.  Mages get a spell that does around 170 dmg 110 mana at lvl 24.  Wizards get one that does around 175 dmg 110 mana.  Now, how insane is that?  Most mages would come back with they don't get DD at every spell level.  My point would be that mages should never get within 5 dmg points of a wizard.  I don't care if we can outdue them in damage by a whopping 50 points at lvl 29.  60 if we use our big spell.  That is 30% more on their off level.  I wonder if a pet makes up for that.  I think it does because you can do damage shield on it and cast in safety while a wizard has no barrier between him and the mob.  The main reason to be a wizard is so that you can cast faster and for a little bit more mana at the expense of having no pet.  You can do about 5-10% more damage over mages on their new DD spell level and all the way up to 30% on their off level.  I thought Ice comet did 1120 400 mana.  Might want to check those numbers.<P>NH-Elhombre<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
