		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 8/14/1999 7:31:00 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=73&FN=Wizard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=383276&TN=Being+wizard+sucks&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=383297&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Just a couple of things...<BR>First off, wizard does not level that slowly if you do it properly. I can reach lvl 6 in a single night, and I hit 16 after only 3 days /play-ed. If you're running into extensive mana problems, your INT is not high enough.  Buy some +INT/+MANA items, or start a character with a higher starting INT (pour all of your points into it).  Someone mentioned in this thread or in another that at 17, they would cast Lightning Bolt and it would take 1 and a quarter bubbles of mana.  My 16 wizard uses 3/4 of a bubble in a cast with 154 INT (after equipment), and this really adds up after casting and casting.<BR>As for solo, it can be done against white mobs.  Make sure you root it. If it fails, root again.  From level 8 onward, if you have a full bar of mana, you can afford to root a few times and still easily have enough to nuke a white mob.  Usually after casting your most powerful spells a couple times a mob will break loose, but then you just need to time slightly weaker spells inbetween blows.  Shock of Ice has served me well up to level 16 because of its casting time/mana/damage ratio.<BR>Of course, there are times when mobs just won't root, and that white mob looks like it's going to beat you to death.  Make sure you leave yourself with some way out... a zone, guards, other people nearby or enough mana for a shadow step/game combo.  Don't wait until you're down to a bar of health to escape.<BR>Wizard is weakest at lvl 1-7, this is true. But if you're only level 10, it is really too early to be complaining about the class.  There is a great deal of money to be made from binding if you look in the right places (almost any dock, especially East Freeport), and it is true that we become a valuable party member later on, particularly between levels 16 and 45.  I do however agree that the mage can be far too close to us in damage spells... at one point they do 5 less damage than us, and that does suck.  I also agree that lvl 45+ wizard needs retooling, as other classes can outdamage us, and practically everything resists our spells.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
